lead_paragraph: Most Californians do not want Gov. Pete Wilson to run for President and if he was the Republican nominee, he would lose in the state to President Clinton, a poll by The Los Angeles Times has found. Sixty-three percent of those surveyed said Mr. Wilson should stay out of the Presidential contest, while 29 percent backed such an effort and 8 percent said they had no opinion, according to the poll published on Sunday.
